{"id": "1497110058067300482", "channel_id": "1497023046496813097", "type": 0, "author_id": "693905974750216212", "author_name": "fishhazardthewizard", "author_bot": false, "content": "yeah the e1 wording implies it adds flat 25% dmg amp directly onto the pre-existing amp, but the math is saying it adds 25% **of** the pre-existing amp onto itself", "timestamp": "2026-04-24T05:40:52.803000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1497023046496813097", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Question about Arachnes E1 scaling calcs", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785", "1361168893200044183"]}
{"id": "1497111029518172221", "channel_id": "1497023046496813097", "type": 0, "author_id": "693905974750216212", "author_name": "fishhazardthewizard", "author_bot": false, "content": "Expected from wording:\n``75% + 25% + 24 * 0.25% = 106%``\n\nObserved/math result (rounding not included):\n``75% + (75(25% + 24 * 0.25%)) = 98.25%``\n\ntranslated the second equation into percentage equivalent to look at more closely", "timestamp": "2026-04-24T05:44:44.415000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1497023046496813097", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Question about Arachnes E1 scaling calcs", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785", "1361168893200044183"]}
